WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.500
Okay, so now I'll be showcasing the features
of being a tournament organizer

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:10.000
and actually setting up these tournaments
and creating a bracket,

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.500
as well as the user side of things,
where they can register for these tournaments.

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:19.000
So firstly, we'll act as a tournament organizer.
We're going to create our own account

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.500
and select Tournament Organizer.

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:25.500
Then, once we're into the actual dashboard,
we can create our own tournament.

00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:30.000
For this, we're just going to create
a weekly tournament,

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
so we can just say "weekly tourney."

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:37.000
For the game, we can just pick one —
let's say Street Fighter.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.500
Okay, so this is us getting
the tournament actually set up.

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:45.500
Obviously, we currently have zero entries
because we just created it.

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:49.000
Now we're going to join this
from the user side,

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:51.500
so we're going to create a user.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:54.000
Okay, then we'll go with Player.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:59.000
From here we can see that the weekly tournament
we created as the organizer account pops up.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:03.000
We can click that
and go sign up for this tourney.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.500
We select our display name,
and it lets us know the game we're playing.

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:10.500
Then we just confirm our registration.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:15.500
Now if we go back to the dashboard,
we can see there's now one entrant — which is us —

00:01:15.500 --> 00:01:18.500
and that's our active tournament.

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:23.000
Now I'll be showcasing that this feature
works on a different size screen.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:29.000
This is simulating a phone, showing our dynamic UI
that can adapt to different browser sizes.
